<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-14T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-14T09:00:00-05:00" n="674" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/2094e</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-14T10:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 14, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1365. From Garfield: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>Notify Garfield’s office and attorneys of all companies
                                        except Texas Company, their manifestations are not to be
                                        filed. They should apply for <hi rend="italic">amparo</hi>
                                        in Mexico City and State of Vera Cruz filing it after August
                                        15 and before August 20. <pb facs="0868" n="756" xml:id="pg_756"/> They should ask for suspension for
                                        reason already known. Suggest they add that power to issue
                                        regulations under Section 1, Article 89, Constitution
                                        supposes preexisting law and as there is not such a law of
                                        Congress legal regulations could not be issued. Notify them
                                        all American companies except Texas unanimously refuse to
                                        file returns.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>